1
00:02:52,760 --> 00:02:54,440
You're kind of heavy, you know.

2
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:57,120
- Then put me down.
- I'm just kidding.

3
00:03:04,320 --> 00:03:05,240
You Mad Dogs!

4
00:03:05,320 --> 00:03:06,680
Stop!

5
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:11,040
Pud is dead.

6
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:16,080
<i>If Mr. Wayu ends up hurting you,</i>
<i>can it be me instead?</i>

7
00:03:17,080 --> 00:03:20,680
<i>I have never been involved with drugs.</i>

8
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:23,080
Why the hell is he saying
all this bullshit?

9
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:24,240
He said we'd fight together.

10
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:29,760
You're this disgusting,
and you dare mess with my sister?

11
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:33,840
Even if I'm not a good wife,

12
00:03:34,440 --> 00:03:37,360
at the very least,
I won't leave you alone.

13
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:35,120
It's been forever already.

14
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:37,720
What are they even doing in there?

15
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:47,840
They're definitely doing
"jookkadik jookkadik" for sure.

16
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:53,480
Well, that's how newlyweds are.

17
00:05:57,040 --> 00:06:00,160
Ugh! Why the heck have I been sitting here
waiting like an idiot this whole time?

18
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:04,120
Ms. Fahsai? Which room is it anyway?

19
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:07,560
I'm heading out first, okay?

20
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:11,080
Oh.

21
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:14,120
Then what am I supposed
to report back to him?

22
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:21,120
If the phone's off,
then there's no problem.

23
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:12,360
Make this case as heavy as possible.

24
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:17,200
I want Wayu locked up
for the rest of his life.

25
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:22,000
Don't worry. I can handle it.

26
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,120
Good.

27
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:27,920
If I can deliver results like this,

28
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:31,520
then maybe it's finally time for you

29
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:33,600
to marry my daughter?

30
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:40,880
Sure.

31
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:42,240
That's easy.

32
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:47,440
But let's wrap this case up nicely first.

33
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:05,640
I have another meeting to get to,
so I'll excuse myself.

34
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:10,880
Have the girls take care of the Commander.

35
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,560
And have someone drive him home too.

36
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:56,320
Prapai?

37
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:00,880
Why are you sitting here?

38
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:21,920
I came to tell you…

39
00:10:24,280 --> 00:10:26,080
everyone's at the safe house now.

40
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:36,800
Thank you so much.

41
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:23,720
Thank you all

42
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:26,200
for still being here.

43
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:32,400
And I'm sorry
for dragging you into all this.

44
00:11:36,960 --> 00:11:38,960
From now on,
there won't be a Mad Dog page anymore.

45
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:46,480
I'll give all of you money to start over.

46
00:11:48,280 --> 00:11:50,720
Go do whatever you really want to do.

47
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:52,520
Sam,

48
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:56,560
MIT is accepting applications right now.

49
00:11:58,720 --> 00:12:02,400
With your portfolio,
getting in would be easy.

50
00:12:07,680 --> 00:12:10,240
Phupa, didn't you say you wanted
to open a skateboard shop?

51
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:15,960
Just pick the location.
I'll handle the rest.

52
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:22,560
And you said you wanted to become a farmer

53
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,760
and live a peaceful life.

54
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:29,560
My dad owns several plots of land

55
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:32,360
already prepared for farming.

56
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:34,760
Just tell me which one you want.

57
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:55,600
Good luck.

58
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:01,680
Good luck with what?

59
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:10,880
Luck has never been on our side anyway.

60
00:13:11,560 --> 00:13:14,000
We're the only ones we can rely on.

61
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,640
The two of us know everything now.

62
00:13:23,920 --> 00:13:25,800
Whether you're Wayu

63
00:13:27,560 --> 00:13:28,760
or Peeraka,

64
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:32,560
you're still my big brother.

65
00:13:37,280 --> 00:13:38,880
You're our big brother.

66
00:13:41,760 --> 00:13:44,120
We'll never abandon the Mad Dog Gang.

67
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:47,840
We're gonna fight those bastards together.

68
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:51,880
Mad Dogs

69
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:54,920
don't let themselves get bitten for free.

70
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,560
We'll fight for you,

71
00:13:58,080 --> 00:13:59,720
and we'll fight for Pud.

72
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:03,880
For justice.

73
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:25,560
The Mad Dog Gang will never die!

74
00:14:41,720 --> 00:14:42,640
Dad,

75
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:45,840
this railway project
is worth 9.7 billion baht?

76
00:14:47,840 --> 00:14:49,880
Even though it's a short route,

77
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:52,720
there are five bidders.

78
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:53,920
All major companies.

79
00:14:54,760 --> 00:14:56,680
Did you tell Mr. Chok
to get ready already?

80
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:02,080
This time, our cut

81
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:05,880
has to be bigger
than the last public park project.

82
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:08,600
He knows.

83
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:11,640
The profit split isn't the issue.

84
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:14,920
The problem is the other four bidders

85
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:17,360
all have powerful connections.

86
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:20,360
Have we found anything
about the committee members?

87
00:15:21,360 --> 00:15:22,520
Yes, sir.

88
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:25,640
We're trying to get close to Dr. Sakda,
the project chairman.

89
00:15:27,040 --> 00:15:28,240
And what did he say?

90
00:15:29,880 --> 00:15:32,240
He's very difficult to approach.
He completely shut us out.

91
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:35,400
What's so difficult about that?
It's such a small issue.

92
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:39,040
If you can't get to him directly,

93
00:15:40,280 --> 00:15:41,200
find another way.

94
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:45,880
Nobody in this world is perfect.
Everyone has a weakness.

95
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:49,800
Go find out who the people
close to him are.

96
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:53,040
Yes, sir.

97
00:15:57,360 --> 00:15:58,760
I warned you before

98
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:01,680
not to let your heart play with fire.

99
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:08,000
Fahsai isn't fire.

100
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:11,840
She's warm sunlight.

101
00:16:16,280 --> 00:16:20,760
I never should've dragged her into this
until things got this out of control.

102
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:25,040
So in the end, you really do love her.

103
00:16:32,560 --> 00:16:34,200
Would you give up everything

104
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:37,520
for this woman?

105
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:26,839
Ms. Fahsai.

106
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:34,640
I couldn't find your brother, so I…

107
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:37,000
Wayu went out to take care of something.

108
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:38,280
He should be back later this morning.

109
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:42,520
If you need anything, just let me know.

110
00:17:43,120 --> 00:17:44,360
Excuse me.

111
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:49,120
Can I speak honestly with you?

112
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:56,360
I know you're unhappy
that I married your brother.

113
00:17:58,560 --> 00:18:02,360
You probably don't want to be associated
with politicians. I understand that.

114
00:18:05,680 --> 00:18:07,640
But I want you to know

115
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:11,680
that I really love your brother.

116
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:19,320
I know these things take time.

117
00:18:20,160 --> 00:18:22,600
It's okay if you still
can't accept me yet.

118
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:27,680
But can you give me a chance?

119
00:18:29,480 --> 00:18:32,960
Let me prove whether I'm worthy
of becoming part of your family.

120
00:18:33,040 --> 00:18:34,520
You don't need to say anything.

121
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:52,040
You already are part of our family.

122
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:57,840
Don't worry about what happened before.

123
00:18:58,680 --> 00:19:00,000
Save your energy for something else.

124
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:04,760
There are still many things you both
will have to get through together.

125
00:19:07,640 --> 00:19:10,680
If you mean my father and my brother,

126
00:19:12,040 --> 00:19:13,120
don't worry.

127
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:15,280
Soon enough, they'll understand

128
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:18,640
that Wayu really has nothing
to do with those drugs.

129
00:19:31,280 --> 00:19:34,320
- There. Speak of the devil.
- Yeah.

130
00:19:38,720 --> 00:19:41,440
I was inviting Fahsai
to breakfast with us.

131
00:19:46,600 --> 00:19:48,200
Can I call you my big sister?

132
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:52,800
Of course.

133
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:55,520
Then let's go.

134
00:19:58,800 --> 00:20:00,080
Come eat with us too, brother.

135
00:20:01,320 --> 00:20:02,240
Brother?

136
00:20:03,040 --> 00:20:04,720
Isn't that what you wanted me to call you?

137
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:09,280
From now on, you're my brother.

138
00:20:14,080 --> 00:20:15,200
Let's go.

139
00:20:40,360 --> 00:20:45,960
32 MISSED CALLS FROM MAYSA

140
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:22,360
Maysa.

141
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:26,280
Maysa.

142
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:37,440
Why didn't you answer my calls?

143
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:51,760
Samut did this to you?

144
00:22:00,040 --> 00:22:03,760
Yesterday, I called you so many times,
but you never answered.

145
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:12,400
I caught him sleeping with my manager.

146
00:22:13,240 --> 00:22:16,480
When I confronted her, he beat me up.

147
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:24,040
You once told me that if he ever laid
a hand on me, you wouldn't let it slide.

148
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:35,160
Let's go to the hospital. I'll take you.

149
00:22:36,160 --> 00:22:37,360
I'm not going.

150
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:43,160
How am I supposed
to face anyone looking like this?

151
00:22:44,320 --> 00:22:47,480
A famous actress getting beaten up
by a politician boyfriend.

152
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:50,200
I'll become gossip
for the rest of my life.

153
00:22:50,280 --> 00:22:52,880
I'm done with him.
I'm breaking up with him.

154
00:22:57,320 --> 00:23:00,560
Dad, I'll work
and take care of you myself.

155
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:04,000
We won't go back
to struggling again, okay?

156
00:23:12,560 --> 00:23:16,880
It's… It's not that simple.

157
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:24,080
You know how powerful
their connections are.

158
00:23:28,440 --> 00:23:30,400
If we go against them now,

159
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:34,640
they'll destroy us
until we have nothing left.

160
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:42,560
Just endure it a little longer.

161
00:23:44,840 --> 00:23:47,160
Wait until I have more power first.

162
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:51,000
And when will that be?

163
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:58,360
You can see what state I'm in.

164
00:23:58,960 --> 00:24:00,520
How much longer do I have
to let him walk all over me?

165
00:24:00,600 --> 00:24:03,720
How much longer do I have
to live without any dignity?

166
00:24:19,520 --> 00:24:21,760
I just finished
handling something for him.

167
00:24:24,040 --> 00:24:26,280
He already promised me
that he'll marry you.

168
00:24:27,520 --> 00:24:30,240
You want me to marry him?

169
00:24:31,120 --> 00:24:35,080
Aren't you worried
he'll kill me someday?

170
00:24:39,080 --> 00:24:39,920
No.

171
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:44,280
He won't dare hurt you again.

172
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:46,760
I have a way.

173
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:48,760
What way?

174
00:24:48,840 --> 00:24:50,080
You don't need to know.

175
00:24:51,400 --> 00:24:52,360
Just trust me.

176
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:57,080
Stay quiet and let me handle everything.

177
00:24:58,480 --> 00:25:00,040
What makes you so confident?

178
00:25:01,760 --> 00:25:04,280
Someone like him fears no one.

179
00:25:05,080 --> 00:25:07,440
- He's evil.
- Just wait and see.

180
00:25:11,160 --> 00:25:14,160
Starting with the fact that he's going
to marry you as soon as possible.

181
00:25:19,760 --> 00:25:21,000
Yong.

182
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:29,960
Where are you taking Fahsai's luggage?

183
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:33,640
Well…

184
00:25:34,840 --> 00:25:36,560
Where is my daughter?

185
00:25:40,480 --> 00:25:42,680
Maybe she's in your heart?

186
00:25:44,080 --> 00:25:45,560
Where is she?

187
00:25:50,640 --> 00:25:52,960
Mr. Samut, Commander--

188
00:25:53,040 --> 00:25:55,120
You beat my daughter up that badly.

189
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:56,360
How are you going
to take responsibility for this?

190
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:12,320
I've cleaned up and buried
countless cases for you already.

191
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:16,680
I just handled that setup
involving Wayu for you too.

192
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:20,080
And this is how you repay me
and my daughter?

193
00:26:20,160 --> 00:26:23,880
Did your daughter
tell you the whole story?

194
00:26:26,880 --> 00:26:29,160
Did she tell you she was the one
who attacked me first?

195
00:26:29,240 --> 00:26:32,200
My daughter's tiny.
What could she possibly do to you?

196
00:26:33,280 --> 00:26:34,600
But you're a man.

197
00:26:34,680 --> 00:26:36,680
You punched my daughter in the face

198
00:26:36,760 --> 00:26:38,640
until she ended up swollen like that.
How could you do that?

199
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:44,200
Are you accusing me
of assaulting your daughter?

200
00:26:45,680 --> 00:26:47,720
Don't you dare cross the line with me.

201
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:49,600
If I hadn't given you jobs,

202
00:26:49,680 --> 00:26:52,800
if I hadn't bribed
your superiors with money,

203
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:55,360
you'd still just be some nobody captain.

204
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:57,720
And your daughter
would still be some useless extra

205
00:26:57,800 --> 00:26:59,720
I could throw away anytime I want.

206
00:27:09,640 --> 00:27:11,600
Looks like you forgot about this clip.

207
00:27:19,120 --> 00:27:20,560
You!

208
00:27:20,640 --> 00:27:23,320
A piece of trash like you
deserves someone like me.

209
00:27:23,400 --> 00:27:25,080
That's what makes us a perfect match.

210
00:27:27,800 --> 00:27:29,120
If I go down,

211
00:27:29,880 --> 00:27:31,760
you think you'll survive?

212
00:27:31,840 --> 00:27:33,360
Am I in the clip?

213
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:36,960
If I'm not, then I survive.

214
00:27:38,720 --> 00:27:40,360
If anything happens to me, I told my men

215
00:27:40,440 --> 00:27:41,360
it was you.

216
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:46,400
And I'm not stupid enough
to keep that clip in only one place.

217
00:27:59,320 --> 00:28:00,360
Behave yourself.

218
00:28:03,040 --> 00:28:05,280
Marry my daughter within this week.

219
00:28:06,840 --> 00:28:11,080
Don't you ever hurt my daughter again.

220
00:28:15,960 --> 00:28:17,120
Then there won't be

221
00:28:17,840 --> 00:28:19,680
any problems between us.

222
00:28:21,120 --> 00:28:22,680
Okay?

223
00:28:40,880 --> 00:28:42,080
Fahsai.

224
00:28:42,160 --> 00:28:43,440
Dad?

225
00:28:45,280 --> 00:28:47,520
- Come home with me right now.
- Dad, not now.

226
00:28:48,360 --> 00:28:50,920
Wayu.

227
00:28:53,080 --> 00:28:54,800
I can't go back yet.

228
00:28:55,520 --> 00:28:58,480
What? You want
to get caught in this mess too?

229
00:28:59,800 --> 00:29:04,800
You run a foundation. Have you seen wives
go to prison because of their husbands?

230
00:29:04,880 --> 00:29:06,080
Think, Fahsai.

231
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:08,280
I don't believe Wayu did it.

232
00:29:09,040 --> 00:29:11,720
I'll stand by him
and testify for him if I have to.

233
00:29:12,320 --> 00:29:15,360
But if you do this,
you'll lose your reputation.

234
00:29:17,320 --> 00:29:19,240
Then why do people get married, Dad?

235
00:29:24,320 --> 00:29:27,080
If not to stay by each other's side

236
00:29:27,160 --> 00:29:28,840
through both happiness and suffering?

237
00:29:31,240 --> 00:29:33,760
Whenever I had problems,
Wayu was always there for me.

238
00:29:34,480 --> 00:29:37,320
And now that he's the one struggling,
you want me to turn my back on him?

239
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:39,960
Don't be naive, Fahsai.

240
00:29:41,160 --> 00:29:44,480
If there were no benefits involved,
do you think Wayu would've helped you?

241
00:29:45,400 --> 00:29:46,800
Your marriage

242
00:29:47,760 --> 00:29:48,920
is about benefits.

243
00:29:49,840 --> 00:29:50,880
Have you forgotten that?

244
00:29:53,360 --> 00:29:55,400
- Let's go.
- Dad.

245
00:29:58,120 --> 00:30:00,160
In your eyes, maybe that's all it is.

246
00:30:01,240 --> 00:30:02,800
But not to me.

247
00:30:06,920 --> 00:30:08,160
Don't worry.

248
00:30:08,840 --> 00:30:11,440
I'll still fulfill my duties
as your daughter.

249
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:13,840
I'll continue working at the foundation.

250
00:30:15,120 --> 00:30:16,160
But I'm staying here.

251
00:30:17,480 --> 00:30:19,200
And I will not abandon my husband.

252
00:30:28,280 --> 00:30:29,600
Hello, Father.

253
00:30:32,880 --> 00:30:35,480
Thank you so much
for worrying about both of us.

254
00:30:39,120 --> 00:30:42,960
But I promise you,
I'll take good care of Fahsai.

255
00:30:45,040 --> 00:30:48,040
She will never become
the wife of a drug dealer

256
00:30:48,920 --> 00:30:50,840
because I would never
do something that evil.

257
00:30:57,160 --> 00:30:58,320
Hello, Minister Rakchart.

258
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:00,640
Would you like to stay for a meal with us?

259
00:31:19,040 --> 00:31:21,440
<i>Annyeonghaseyo.</i>

260
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:38,600
What are you doing here?
We have nothing left to talk about.

261
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:41,920
I'm not here to see you.
I'm here to see Mr. Wayu.

262
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:55,120
I'm here to ask some additional questions.

263
00:31:56,480 --> 00:31:57,320
Please, have a seat.

264
00:31:58,240 --> 00:31:59,280
Thank you.

265
00:32:07,240 --> 00:32:09,880
Copies of every restaurant employee's
ID card.

266
00:32:10,640 --> 00:32:12,200
The ones your officers requested.

267
00:32:12,280 --> 00:32:13,760
Thank you.

268
00:32:13,840 --> 00:32:16,360
If you're here to question me
about the drugs,

269
00:32:17,240 --> 00:32:18,440
I have nothing else to say.

270
00:32:20,160 --> 00:32:21,760
I'm asking for your cooperation.

271
00:32:23,720 --> 00:32:25,120
The reason I won't say anything

272
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:29,160
is because police like you
probably won't believe me anyway.

273
00:32:30,440 --> 00:32:33,040
So let's just look
at the physical evidence.

274
00:32:56,600 --> 00:33:00,400
This man definitely isn't one
of my restaurant employees.

275
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:06,480
He probably has
a criminal record somewhere.

276
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:13,480
Does he look familiar to you?

277
00:33:26,720 --> 00:33:27,800
Yes, Sergeant?

278
00:33:27,880 --> 00:33:30,640
Captain, Commander Singha
wants to see you immediately.

279
00:33:38,760 --> 00:33:40,200
<i>Why hasn't this case moved forward?</i>

280
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:42,280
What are you waiting for?

281
00:33:42,960 --> 00:33:44,920
You know we can't delay this.

282
00:33:45,760 --> 00:33:48,840
We need to finish the report
and send it to the prosecutor the soonest.

283
00:33:49,640 --> 00:33:51,840
The faster we close this case,

284
00:33:51,920 --> 00:33:54,120
the safer the public will feel.

285
00:33:55,280 --> 00:33:57,760
And right now, reporters
are swarming outside our unit.

286
00:33:58,400 --> 00:34:00,200
We need answers for them.

287
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:02,880
Then you can go down
and speak to the reporters.

288
00:34:02,960 --> 00:34:05,240
Because I just got
a new piece of evidence.

289
00:34:37,800 --> 00:34:39,520
If this clip gets out,

290
00:34:40,520 --> 00:34:43,360
who exactly do you think
will end up standing trial?

291
00:34:43,440 --> 00:34:47,080
Mr. Wayu or your subordinates?

292
00:34:49,880 --> 00:34:52,600
When I first saw this clip, I was furious.

293
00:34:52,679 --> 00:34:54,040
Because the culprit is a police officer.

294
00:34:55,040 --> 00:34:59,640
But why do you
seem so calm about it, Commander?

295
00:35:01,200 --> 00:35:02,600
Or did you already know?

296
00:35:04,240 --> 00:35:05,360
What are you talking about?

297
00:35:05,440 --> 00:35:08,520
Then allow me to show the reporters
evidence of the police planting drugs.

298
00:35:09,160 --> 00:35:11,760
Because this is the progress of my work

299
00:35:11,840 --> 00:35:14,040
and the progress of this case.

300
00:35:15,040 --> 00:35:16,160
Excuse me.

301
00:35:17,800 --> 00:35:18,840
You can't!

302
00:35:25,840 --> 00:35:29,320
We will investigate the truth about this.

303
00:35:30,400 --> 00:35:33,080
But we cannot release it to outsiders.

304
00:35:33,160 --> 00:35:34,560
This is about the image
of the police force.

305
00:35:35,960 --> 00:35:39,040
You are strictly forbidden
from saying anything to the press.

306
00:35:40,040 --> 00:35:41,680
I'll handle it myself.

307
00:35:41,760 --> 00:35:43,520
But I won't lie.

308
00:35:43,600 --> 00:35:44,880
This is an order!

309
00:35:46,240 --> 00:35:48,400
Say nothing.

310
00:38:13,760 --> 00:38:15,240
Follow him!

311
00:38:24,560 --> 00:38:25,920
Hurry!

312
00:38:38,120 --> 00:38:39,560
Hey!

313
00:38:41,120 --> 00:38:42,200
Follow him.

314
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:20,000
How did you know
someone was waiting to shoot me?

315
00:40:22,760 --> 00:40:25,960
You know who ordered the hit on you,
don't you?

316
00:40:34,640 --> 00:40:35,720
How does it feel

317
00:40:36,840 --> 00:40:38,480
being betrayed by someone you trusted?

318
00:40:41,680 --> 00:40:42,640
Why did you help me?

319
00:40:48,480 --> 00:40:50,840
I've known you longer than you think.

320
00:40:54,160 --> 00:40:56,200
I've known you
since you were a lieutenant.

321
00:40:57,440 --> 00:40:59,000
You're a good man.

322
00:41:01,160 --> 00:41:03,040
But everyone around you

323
00:41:04,520 --> 00:41:05,720
is rotten.

324
00:41:07,680 --> 00:41:09,520
No matter how much good you do,
nobody sees it.

325
00:41:11,040 --> 00:41:13,560
What do you mean
you've known me for a long time?

326
00:41:17,360 --> 00:41:18,800
How's Kaitod,

327
00:41:20,680 --> 00:41:21,760
your dog?

328
00:41:24,040 --> 00:41:25,920
Did Prapai tell you about my dog too?

329
00:41:27,040 --> 00:41:29,480
I knew Kaitod before I even met Prapai.

330
00:41:32,440 --> 00:41:34,280
You named him Kaitod

331
00:41:36,560 --> 00:41:38,880
because it was
your girlfriend's favorite food.

332
00:41:40,680 --> 00:41:41,920
How do you know that?

333
00:41:47,640 --> 00:41:49,200
Do you remember

334
00:41:51,120 --> 00:41:52,840
how you met your girlfriend
for the first time?

335
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:16,640
My eyes just sting.

336
00:42:29,440 --> 00:42:31,880
A child got beaten
by his father that badly.

337
00:42:31,960 --> 00:42:33,960
Anyone who saw it would cry.

338
00:42:35,360 --> 00:42:37,160
On my first day at work,

339
00:42:37,240 --> 00:42:39,600
I went through an entire box of tissues.

340
00:42:41,600 --> 00:42:42,800
So just cry.

341
00:42:44,040 --> 00:42:45,760
Police officers have hearts too.

342
00:42:47,640 --> 00:42:49,840
Having a heart is a good thing.

343
00:43:01,160 --> 00:43:02,320
Because of that packet of tissues,

344
00:43:07,520 --> 00:43:11,360
you kept buying her things to thank her.

345
00:43:14,120 --> 00:43:17,040
Then you asked her to be your girlfriend
on her birthday.

346
00:43:20,280 --> 00:43:22,240
And the birthday gift you gave her

347
00:43:22,320 --> 00:43:24,320
made her tease you for a whole year.

348
00:43:30,840 --> 00:43:32,720
Happy birthday, Kul.

349
00:43:32,800 --> 00:43:34,320
Here, your birthday present.

350
00:43:34,960 --> 00:43:38,080
- Ugh? This is my birthday present?
- Yes.

351
00:43:38,880 --> 00:43:44,320
Whenever you sleep and turn over,
you'll see my face all night long.

352
00:43:46,240 --> 00:43:49,040
If I had to look at this all night,
I'd have nightmares. No.

353
00:43:49,120 --> 00:43:53,000
Whoa, that's harsh. What nightmares?
Sweet dreams, obviously.

354
00:43:53,080 --> 00:43:56,120
I'm dark, tall, and handsome.

355
00:43:58,280 --> 00:43:59,920
These days, girls like

356
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:02,680
fair, slim Korean-looking guys, Uncle.

357
00:44:02,760 --> 00:44:04,280
- Whoa.
- I don't want that.

358
00:44:04,360 --> 00:44:06,280
Please, Kul. Please?

359
00:44:06,360 --> 00:44:07,920
- Please.
- No.

360
00:44:08,000 --> 00:44:10,080
- Please.
- No.

361
00:44:10,680 --> 00:44:12,440
How do you know about all this?

362
00:44:14,440 --> 00:44:15,880
This was between me and Kul.

363
00:44:17,000 --> 00:44:18,600
No outsider could know any of this.

364
00:44:29,480 --> 00:44:31,120
Because I'm not an outsider.

365
00:44:35,360 --> 00:44:37,280
You should've proposed to Kul sooner.

366
00:44:39,120 --> 00:44:41,080
You should've gone on your honeymoon
and had children with her,

367
00:44:41,960 --> 00:44:44,640
lived happily together,
made Kul as happy as possible.

368
00:44:50,440 --> 00:44:52,120
Kul loved you so much.

369
00:44:58,440 --> 00:45:00,400
She told me she wanted to get married.

370
00:45:02,080 --> 00:45:03,600
Once she got married,

371
00:45:06,240 --> 00:45:07,760
she was going to quit her job

372
00:45:09,600 --> 00:45:11,240
and take care of you and your children.

373
00:45:14,400 --> 00:45:16,680
If she'd quit that damn job,

374
00:45:19,520 --> 00:45:21,200
things wouldn't have ended this way.

375
00:45:44,840 --> 00:45:46,080
Raka?

376
00:46:00,320 --> 00:46:03,240
Kul had made you a birthday gift too.

377
00:46:06,440 --> 00:46:08,280
She knitted a scarf for you.

378
00:46:11,800 --> 00:46:13,640
She kept showing it off to me.

379
00:46:19,040 --> 00:46:21,760
But she never got the chance
to give it to you.

380
00:46:25,800 --> 00:46:28,400
Everything was lost in that fire.

381
00:46:29,920 --> 00:46:33,480
That scarf… Kul…

382
00:46:35,560 --> 00:46:37,120
and Mom.

383
00:46:52,680 --> 00:46:53,640
It's okay.

384
00:47:01,280 --> 00:47:02,400
Raka…

385
00:47:04,520 --> 00:47:05,760
It really is you.

386
00:47:14,520 --> 00:47:17,400
I'm sorry, Raka.

387
00:47:19,800 --> 00:47:23,320
I was so consumed by grief
that I let so much time pass.

388
00:47:25,040 --> 00:47:26,920
I should've searched for the truth sooner.

389
00:47:33,080 --> 00:47:34,080
I'm sorry.

390
00:47:44,160 --> 00:47:45,920
But it's not too late

391
00:47:48,000 --> 00:47:49,440
if we work together.

392
00:47:53,520 --> 00:47:54,600
For Kul.

393
00:48:13,760 --> 00:48:15,680
I was about to bring the drinks in.

394
00:48:16,400 --> 00:48:17,760
Or does Wayu want anything else?

395
00:48:17,840 --> 00:48:20,000
I understand now
why you love your brother like a lover.

396
00:48:21,320 --> 00:48:23,160
You already knew he was Peeraka.

397
00:48:24,920 --> 00:48:26,480
Now I'm not surprised anymore

398
00:48:27,600 --> 00:48:30,600
why you… love him.

399
00:48:34,400 --> 00:48:36,080
Hey.

400
00:48:55,440 --> 00:48:58,520
Have you really come to terms
with Mr. Wayu and Ms. Fahsai?

401
00:49:00,560 --> 00:49:02,480
I have to.

402
00:49:02,560 --> 00:49:04,200
They love each other that much.

403
00:49:06,800 --> 00:49:09,960
And honestly, even without Fahsai,

404
00:49:11,640 --> 00:49:14,040
I know Wayu could never love me
romantically anyway.

405
00:49:16,440 --> 00:49:19,640
- Because?
- Because he loves me like a sister.

406
00:49:21,520 --> 00:49:23,560
No matter how good I am to him,

407
00:49:23,640 --> 00:49:26,160
or even if I kneel down and beg him,

408
00:49:27,120 --> 00:49:28,440
he won't give in.

409
00:49:30,480 --> 00:49:31,800
Like me and you.

410
00:49:33,560 --> 00:49:35,800
Is that what you're trying
to tell me indirectly?

411
00:49:38,160 --> 00:49:40,800
Not indirectly. I'm saying it outright.

412
00:49:43,440 --> 00:49:45,320
I love you like a brother.

413
00:49:47,960 --> 00:49:49,440
Besides Dad and Wayu,

414
00:49:50,800 --> 00:49:54,160
you're the one
who's always taken care of me.

415
00:49:57,080 --> 00:49:59,160
You're another big brother to me.

416
00:50:02,680 --> 00:50:04,080
I understand.

417
00:50:16,760 --> 00:50:18,080
Thank you, Praya,

418
00:50:20,000 --> 00:50:21,960
for everything…

419
00:50:24,280 --> 00:50:25,640
especially when it comes to love.

420
00:50:28,680 --> 00:50:32,480
You taught me
that we can't force someone's heart.

421
00:50:42,680 --> 00:50:44,160
Looking back,

422
00:50:47,160 --> 00:50:49,560
Wayu must've felt so suffocated,

423
00:50:51,520 --> 00:50:53,400
having me beg him to love me for years.

424
00:51:05,880 --> 00:51:07,520
Do you really understand what I'm saying?

425
00:51:11,320 --> 00:51:13,560
I really do love
this older brother of mine, okay?

426
00:51:16,640 --> 00:51:17,880
Do you understand now?

427
00:51:20,280 --> 00:51:21,480
Do you?

428
00:51:26,640 --> 00:51:28,320
I understand, little sister.

429
00:51:29,840 --> 00:51:31,480
But give me a little time to get over it.

430
00:51:31,560 --> 00:51:35,160
How many days? It only took me two.

431
00:51:37,600 --> 00:51:38,880
Well…

432
00:51:39,520 --> 00:51:41,960
You're strong,
just like Boss Chaichana's daughter.

433
00:51:43,240 --> 00:51:44,280
But don't worry.

434
00:51:46,400 --> 00:51:48,320
I'll be a good big brother to you.

435
00:51:49,680 --> 00:51:51,720
I won't lose to Mr. Wayu.

436
00:51:58,160 --> 00:51:59,400
- Hey.
- Hm?

437
00:52:01,440 --> 00:52:03,160
You're being this cheerful.

438
00:52:05,080 --> 00:52:07,200
Is it because
you've gotten over one person

439
00:52:08,880 --> 00:52:10,960
and started falling for someone else?

440
00:52:12,320 --> 00:52:13,160
Huh?

441
00:52:18,280 --> 00:52:20,960
The trees in our house
look really green today.

442
00:52:25,240 --> 00:52:26,800
They're green every day, aren't they?

443
00:52:29,360 --> 00:52:30,800
So,

444
00:52:32,800 --> 00:52:34,120
do you have feelings for someone or not?

445
00:52:41,280 --> 00:52:44,840
From what I found out,
Aey, Kul's senior, said

446
00:52:44,920 --> 00:52:46,920
Kul took the evidence clip

447
00:52:47,000 --> 00:52:51,360
of Mahasamut blackmailing an actress
to Commander Singha.

448
00:52:53,360 --> 00:52:55,680
Back then, Kul trusted
Commander Singha the most.

449
00:53:02,560 --> 00:53:04,080
After I dated May,

450
00:53:06,040 --> 00:53:09,520
I found out later that Commander Singha
used to be close friends with my father.

451
00:53:10,120 --> 00:53:13,280
That's why Kul trusted him.
But Samut must've used money

452
00:53:13,960 --> 00:53:15,400
and influence to shut him up.

453
00:53:16,280 --> 00:53:17,480
There's one more important thing.

454
00:53:18,520 --> 00:53:21,680
Ms. Fahsai once came to me
and asked me to reinvestigate your case.

455
00:53:23,040 --> 00:53:24,880
She wanted to clear your name.

456
00:53:26,800 --> 00:53:29,440
She didn't believe
you were the one who killed your family.

457
00:53:39,920 --> 00:53:42,320
You approached the Minister's family

458
00:53:44,280 --> 00:53:45,240
to expose the truth, right?

459
00:53:47,160 --> 00:53:48,840
And Ms. Fahsai doesn't know about this?

460
00:53:53,920 --> 00:53:54,920
I can't tell her.

461
00:53:58,880 --> 00:54:00,880
I still can't let her know I'm Peeraka,

462
00:54:03,120 --> 00:54:05,000
because no matter what,
she's still his daughter

463
00:54:06,120 --> 00:54:07,160
and Samut's sister.

464
00:54:11,040 --> 00:54:12,680
I was willing to do anything.

465
00:54:14,600 --> 00:54:16,880
I was willing to change myself
to get revenge on them.

466
00:54:18,080 --> 00:54:20,960
I won't let my plan fall apart
because of anyone.

467
00:54:21,040 --> 00:54:23,160
I won't tell Ms. Fahsai.

468
00:54:24,840 --> 00:54:25,920
But how are we going to find evidence?

469
00:54:26,720 --> 00:54:29,360
Singha must've kept
that evidence somewhere safe.

470
00:54:31,160 --> 00:54:32,800
Because it's the only thing

471
00:54:32,880 --> 00:54:34,800
that can take Mahasamut down.

472
00:54:38,200 --> 00:54:39,760
I have people who can help us.

473
00:54:58,560 --> 00:55:00,560
I know our methods

474
00:55:01,200 --> 00:55:02,640
may not sit well with you.

475
00:55:03,920 --> 00:55:06,240
But we do this to expose evil people.

476
00:55:08,080 --> 00:55:10,240
When evil people hold power

477
00:55:11,480 --> 00:55:13,480
and have enough money
to turn good people bad…

478
00:55:14,680 --> 00:55:15,960
We created the page

479
00:55:16,040 --> 00:55:19,120
because we believed it could be a voice
for people who were being bullied.

480
00:55:21,040 --> 00:55:23,960
You saw what they did, Captain.

481
00:55:25,240 --> 00:55:27,480
They ordered people killed
without feeling any guilt.

482
00:55:28,600 --> 00:55:29,720
Sometimes,

483
00:55:30,360 --> 00:55:32,680
waiting for the law to punish
people this evil is too slow.

484
00:55:33,800 --> 00:55:35,640
As long as it's a method
that doesn't hurt anyone

485
00:55:37,040 --> 00:55:38,280
and gets us the evidence,

486
00:55:40,360 --> 00:55:42,880
I have no problem working with you.

487
00:56:01,240 --> 00:56:03,240
- Hey.
- Hey, the Mad Dogs are here.

488
00:56:06,520 --> 00:56:08,640
Hi, everyone.

489
00:56:08,720 --> 00:56:10,440
Hello, everyone.

490
00:56:10,520 --> 00:56:11,800
We're back.

491
00:56:12,520 --> 00:56:14,000
Do you still remember us?

492
00:56:14,080 --> 00:56:17,400
Their old page got shut down.
What's the new page called?

493
00:56:17,480 --> 00:56:20,400
Mad Dog Never Dies.

494
00:56:22,160 --> 00:56:24,160
We're back, and this time,
we're going harder

495
00:56:24,240 --> 00:56:25,760
and bigger than ever.

496
00:56:27,280 --> 00:56:29,360
Whoever said we're full of shit

497
00:56:29,440 --> 00:56:30,680
and lie to people,

498
00:56:30,760 --> 00:56:33,160
we're here to get payback.

499
00:56:34,040 --> 00:56:37,080
How should we get payback?

500
00:56:37,680 --> 00:56:39,440
Then we have to start with this clip.

501
00:56:39,520 --> 00:56:42,120
Come on, see it with your own eyes.

502
00:56:43,520 --> 00:56:45,840
MAD DOG IS BACK

503
00:56:45,920 --> 00:56:48,200
I THOUGHT YOU'D GIVE UP THIS PAGE

504
00:56:48,280 --> 00:56:50,720
MAKE IT HARDER THIS TIME

505
00:56:50,800 --> 00:56:52,840
LONG LIVE MAD DOG.

506
00:56:54,240 --> 00:56:56,720
- Who the hell is that?
- Want to know, right?

507
00:56:58,080 --> 00:56:59,120
Show them.

508
00:56:59,960 --> 00:57:01,840
WHO IS THAT?

509
00:57:01,920 --> 00:57:05,640
DON'T TELL ME…

510
00:57:10,840 --> 00:57:12,800
Netizen friends, open your eyes and look.

511
00:57:12,880 --> 00:57:16,160
If these faces don't match,
circle the difference with a pen.

512
00:57:17,720 --> 00:57:18,840
This is planting drugs.

513
00:57:19,960 --> 00:57:22,680
I knew it. Those dogs
weren't selling drugs.

514
00:57:22,760 --> 00:57:24,040
They were selling spicy salad.

515
00:57:24,120 --> 00:57:26,080
<i>So the Mad Dog Gang was framed.</i>

516
00:57:26,160 --> 00:57:27,800
<i>The real liars are the police?</i>

517
00:57:27,880 --> 00:57:29,640
<i>Fire the whole damn department.</i>

518
00:57:29,720 --> 00:57:31,440
<i>The Mad Dogs are the real heroes.</i>

519
00:57:31,520 --> 00:57:33,000
<i>Spoil the ending too.</i>

520
00:57:33,080 --> 00:57:34,320
<i>Do the police go to jail?</i>

521
00:57:34,400 --> 00:57:37,360
<i>My four-chambered heart</i>
<i>belongs to all four of you.</i>

522
00:57:37,440 --> 00:57:39,880
<i>Thank you, my beloved Mad Dogs.</i>

523
00:57:39,960 --> 00:57:41,600
We have to thank everyone

524
00:57:42,120 --> 00:57:43,640
for still standing with us.

525
00:57:44,920 --> 00:57:48,560
Evil people must pay for
what they've done.

526
00:57:48,640 --> 00:57:50,240
Not just for planting drugs,

527
00:57:51,400 --> 00:57:53,320
but for causing an innocent person to die.

528
00:57:53,400 --> 00:57:56,400
Those bastards
must have no place in society.

529
00:57:57,120 --> 00:57:58,440
Poodle must not have died for nothing.

530
00:58:00,040 --> 00:58:01,600
<i>RIP Poodle.</i>

531
00:58:01,680 --> 00:58:03,240
<i>RIP Poodle.</i>

532
00:58:03,320 --> 00:58:04,640
<i>RIP Poodle.</i>

533
00:58:05,360 --> 00:58:08,680
But the bad news is,

534
00:58:09,680 --> 00:58:11,520
two police officers are dead.

535
00:58:12,120 --> 00:58:13,200
One has disappeared.

536
00:58:13,760 --> 00:58:15,760
Dead and missing

537
00:58:15,840 --> 00:58:17,880
right after evidence surfaced
that they planted drugs?

538
00:58:18,480 --> 00:58:20,680
Help us put the puzzle pieces together.

539
00:58:20,760 --> 00:58:22,480
What do you think happened?

540
00:58:22,560 --> 00:58:24,320
<i>Payback?</i>

541
00:58:24,400 --> 00:58:25,800
<i>Silenced, obviously.</i>

542
00:58:25,880 --> 00:58:27,480
<i>Murdered.</i>

543
00:58:27,560 --> 00:58:30,360
<i>Ordered hit. Afraid it would</i>
<i>lead back to the big boss.</i>

544
00:58:30,440 --> 00:58:32,000
Wow.

545
00:58:32,080 --> 00:58:35,400
This comment is wondering
the same thing as us.

546
00:58:36,040 --> 00:58:39,280
Who gave the order?
And who's the big boss?

547
00:58:39,360 --> 00:58:40,840
We're dying to know.

548
00:58:48,800 --> 00:58:49,760
What is it, Sergeant?

549
00:58:52,280 --> 00:58:54,560
What? The Commander
wants to see me immediately?

550
00:58:57,840 --> 00:59:00,720
I think they followed me
ever since I left the unit.

551
00:59:00,800 --> 00:59:04,160
Three men. Two motorcycles. Fully armed.

552
00:59:04,240 --> 00:59:05,200
Oh.

553
00:59:05,280 --> 00:59:08,560
So you handled
all three suspects by yourself, Captain?

554
00:59:09,960 --> 00:59:12,000
While I was defending myself,

555
00:59:13,080 --> 00:59:14,880
a man came and saved my life.

556
00:59:14,960 --> 00:59:16,000
That's why I survived.

557
00:59:16,080 --> 00:59:19,680
Commander, how will you deal
with the suspect who disappeared?

558
00:59:19,760 --> 00:59:21,960
We're urgently tracking him down.

559
00:59:22,040 --> 00:59:25,560
Will the investigation be expanded
to uncover the mastermind behind all this?

560
00:59:26,360 --> 00:59:30,280
Well, we're still conducting
further investigations

561
00:59:30,880 --> 00:59:32,800
because the case is complicated.

562
00:59:33,440 --> 00:59:35,880
It's no longer
just a simple drug-planting case.

563
00:59:35,960 --> 00:59:39,040
There was also an attempt
to silence the officer

564
00:59:39,120 --> 00:59:40,760
responsible for the case.

565
00:59:41,800 --> 00:59:45,160
So we need more time
to uncover the truth.

566
00:59:45,240 --> 00:59:48,160
But we'll do our best.

567
00:59:49,560 --> 00:59:53,960
<i>I'd also like to apologize to the public</i>

568
00:59:54,680 --> 00:59:57,080
<i>because this incident happened</i>
<i>within my department.</i>

569
00:59:57,880 --> 01:00:01,480
<i>I'm fully prepared to take responsibility</i>

570
01:00:02,040 --> 01:00:05,960
<i>in whatever way my superiors see fit.</i>

571
01:00:09,040 --> 01:00:10,320
Wow.

572
01:00:11,080 --> 01:00:13,560
Police Officer of the Year!

573
01:00:13,640 --> 01:00:14,880
See that?

574
01:00:14,960 --> 01:00:17,360
Taking responsibility for his men.

575
01:00:17,440 --> 01:00:19,080
You won't find another one like him.

576
01:00:19,160 --> 01:00:22,720
Maybe we should stop being Mad Dogs
and become Commander Singha's men.

577
01:00:22,800 --> 01:00:23,840
He's so damn cool.

578
01:00:24,840 --> 01:00:27,640
So what do you guys think?
Drop your comments.

579
01:00:27,720 --> 01:00:29,520
<i>It's rare to see police admit fault.</i>

580
01:00:29,600 --> 01:00:31,440
<i>Usually, they just pass the blame around.</i>

581
01:00:31,520 --> 01:00:33,760
<i>May's dad can do no wrong.</i>

582
01:00:33,840 --> 01:00:35,440
<i>Her dad is still so handsome.</i>

583
01:00:35,520 --> 01:00:38,040
<i>Now I know who May got her face from.</i>

584
01:00:38,640 --> 01:00:40,880
<i>Thai police. Handsome beyond this world.</i>

585
01:00:42,600 --> 01:00:43,840
People believe you quite a lot.

586
01:00:45,920 --> 01:00:49,680
I'm giving it three or four days.
If nothing progresses,

587
01:00:51,120 --> 01:00:52,800
the backlash is going to hit hard.

588
01:00:52,880 --> 01:00:56,600
We can use social media

589
01:00:57,600 --> 01:01:00,760
to manipulate public attention.

590
01:01:02,240 --> 01:01:06,120
Just stir people up to attack someone
or target politicians.

591
01:01:07,240 --> 01:01:09,000
You people

592
01:01:09,080 --> 01:01:11,320
are already good at that anyway.

593
01:01:26,840 --> 01:01:29,600
The love I have for her, even now,

594
01:01:30,360 --> 01:01:31,800
everything is still the same.

595
01:01:34,120 --> 01:01:35,320
You're the only one I love.

596
01:01:38,040 --> 01:01:39,720
And what about our deal?

597
01:01:39,800 --> 01:01:42,560
Well, if May is in the room,
then the deal stands.

598
01:01:42,640 --> 01:01:43,800
Mr. Samut!

599
01:01:43,880 --> 01:01:45,840
Samut was the one who let me in.

600
01:01:45,920 --> 01:01:47,880
No! No!

601
01:01:47,960 --> 01:01:50,000
I'd like to invite you

602
01:01:50,080 --> 01:01:51,880
to give a statement
at police headquarters.

603
01:01:51,960 --> 01:01:53,320
Give a statement?

604
01:01:53,400 --> 01:01:55,200
Don't contact me again.

605
01:01:55,280 --> 01:01:56,440
So now you're just going to throw me away?

606
01:01:56,520 --> 01:01:58,040
Go find someone else to help you.

607
01:01:58,120 --> 01:01:59,240
You fucking bastard!

608
01:01:59,320 --> 01:02:01,040
Did you arrange this with Mr. Samut today?

609
01:02:01,120 --> 01:02:02,480
Samut will be here soon,

610
01:02:02,560 --> 01:02:04,240
so he asked me to take care of the guests.

611
01:02:04,320 --> 01:02:07,600
He asked you to personally
take care of the guests?

612
01:02:07,680 --> 01:02:09,320
No!

613
01:02:09,920 --> 01:02:11,080
Hey!

614
01:02:11,760 --> 01:02:13,000
Come here!

615
01:03:13,520 --> 01:03:15,080
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
